Remind me, what is it you do in Munro?

852
01:09:11,093 --> 01:09:13,089
I haul gravel.

853
01:09:13,099 --> 01:09:14,253
That's a shame.

854
01:09:14,263 --> 01:09:18,691
Think of all the crime that could've
been solved if you'd been on the job.

855
01:09:18,701 --> 01:09:21,927
This goes to trial, the defense
will say you poisoned the well.

856
01:09:21,937 --> 01:09:24,296
-It won't go to trial.
-What?

857
01:09:24,306 --> 01:09:25,931
-It wasn't them.
-I'm sorry?

858
01:09:25,941 --> 01:09:30,169
I don't know why they lied about not
being with him, but they didn't do it.

859
01:09:30,179 --> 01:09:33,105
-They were fighting in the parking lot.
-Blowing off steam.

860
01:09:33,115 --> 01:09:35,841
You have not been to war
so you won't understand this.

861
01:09:35,851 --> 01:09:40,356
You do not fight beside a man
and then do that to him.

862
01:09:40,389 --> 01:09:43,364
That's quite the world you live in.

863
01:09:44,126 --> 01:09:46,126
Find out why they lied.

864
01:09:50,799 --> 01:09:52,799
There'll be a reason.

865
01:10:03,812 --> 01:10:06,022
SANDERS:
So you were there.

866
01:10:06,882 --> 01:10:08,474
Yeah.

867
01:10:08,484 --> 01:10:10,484
So why would you lie?

868
01:10:10,652 --> 01:10:12,711
It's complicated.

869
01:10:13,522 --> 01:10:16,922
Why don't you just tell me
what happened?

870
01:10:21,029 --> 01:10:23,155
We were at this strip club.

871
01:10:23,165 --> 01:10:28,193
Just hanging out, having a good time.
We were drinking, of course.

872
01:10:28,203 --> 01:10:31,263
And Mike starts acting really weird.

873
01:10:31,406 --> 01:10:33,799
Really angry,
throwing change at the stripper.

874
01:10:33,809 --> 01:10:35,567
Then he started talking trash...

875
01:10:35,577 --> 01:10:39,371
...so she started talking trash,
and they tossed us out.

876
01:10:39,381 --> 01:10:41,106
And we're getting in the car...

877
01:10:41,116 --> 01:10:43,876
