And we were riding along...

1209
01:41:04,738 --> 01:41:07,664
...and Mike was pretending
like he was a medic.

1210
01:41:07,674 --> 01:41:11,839
And he would stick his hand
in this guy's wound...

1211
01:41:12,879 --> 01:41:15,672
...and he says, "Does this hurt? "

1212
01:41:15,682 --> 01:41:18,075
And the haji screamed, "Yeah, yeah."

1213
01:41:18,085 --> 01:41:19,977
[PENNING LAUGHS]

1214
01:41:19,987 --> 01:41:23,814
And then Mike would stick his hand
in the exact same place...

1215
01:41:23,824 --> 01:41:26,374
...and say, "Does that hurt? "

1216
01:41:30,797 --> 01:41:32,797
It was pretty funny.

1217
01:41:36,069 --> 01:41:38,469
It became a thing with Mike.

1218
01:41:40,741 --> 01:41:43,546
That's how he got the name "Doc."

1219
01:41:45,245 --> 01:41:47,455
It was just a way to cope.

1220
01:41:49,016 --> 01:41:51,280
We all did stupid things.

1221
01:42:34,728 --> 01:42:36,728
Excuse me, sir.

1222
01:42:55,115 --> 01:42:58,515
You know where Private Ortiez's room is?

1223
01:43:07,861 --> 01:43:09,861
HANK:
You got a minute?

1224
01:43:12,499 --> 01:43:14,794
I need to apologize to you.

1225
01:43:14,968 --> 01:43:17,294
You got some real serious issues, man.

1226
01:43:17,304 --> 01:43:19,304
Yeah.

1227
01:43:20,674 --> 01:43:22,674
That's true.

1228
01:43:32,586 --> 01:43:34,678
[SOLDIERS SINGING
MILITARY CADENCE]

1229
01:43:34,688 --> 01:43:39,049
ORTIEZ: I got a honorable discharge,
if you could believe it.

1230
01:43:39,059 --> 01:43:42,629
HANK:
It's the Army, I'll believe anything.

1231
01:43:43,630 --> 01:43:46,022
ORTIEZ:
I hated it over there.

1232
01:43:46,032 --> 01:43:49,292
Sleep in fucking tents.
No toilets, no showers.

1233
01:43:49,302 --> 01:43:52,635
No toilet paper, gotta use your hand.

1234
01:43:53,340 --> 01:43:55,635
I couldn't wait to get out.

1235
01:43:57,878 --> 01:44:00,176
After two weeks here...

1236
01:44:02,349 --> 01:44:04,874
...all I wanna do is go back.

1237
01:44:07,187 --> 01:44:09,280
How fucked is that?

1238
01:44:19,332 --> 01:44:21,332
You know what that is?

1239
01:44:25,505 --> 01:44:28,031
Mike took it and e-mailed it to me.

1240
01:44:28,041 --> 01:44:30,041
Why would he do that?

1241
01:44:37,217 --> 01:44:40,362
I don't know what anybody's told you.

1242
01:44:41,855 --> 01:44:44,065
There are standing orders.

1243
01:44:44,090 --> 01:44:45,882
You're in a convoy...

1244
01:44:45,892 --> 01:44:49,085
...someone or something gets in front
of you, you do not stop.

1245
01:44:49,095 --> 01:44:54,110
You stop, shitheads pop up
with RPG's and kill you all dead.

1246
01:45:07,380 --> 01:45:09,940
First week in Iraq...

1247
01:45:10,283 --> 01:45:12,683
...we're driving downrange.

1248
01:45:12,853 --> 01:45:14,878
Six of us in the back.

1249
01:45:15,055 --> 01:45:17,690
You can't see squat back there.

1250
01:45:19,960 --> 01:45:21,960
Doc hit something.

1251
01:45:23,763 --> 01:45:26,738
We hear it thump around underneath.

1252
01:45:28,668 --> 01:45:30,594
He stops.

1253
01:45:30,604 --> 01:45:32,604
Gets out.

1254
01:45:33,506 --> 01:45:35,506
Drives on.

1255
01:45:37,477 --> 01:45:39,477
Not a word.

1256
01:45:41,781 --> 01:45:44,079
Later, some guy said...

1257
01:45:44,251 --> 01:45:46,251
...we hit a kid.

1258
01:45:46,653 --> 01:45:48,653
I don't believe it.

1259
01:45:48,922 --> 01:45:50,947
You ask me...

1260
01:45:52,959 --> 01:45:54,959
...we hit a dog.

1261
01:45:56,930 --> 01:45:59,023
We killed a dog.

1262
01:46:02,535 --> 01:46:04,745
I don't know what that is.

1263
01:46:07,641 --> 01:46:09,700
No fucking idea.

1264
01:46:35,402 --> 01:46:38,632
MIKE:
Hey, Bonner, there's your family.

1265
01:46:38,805 --> 01:46:41,164
-Stop fucking around!
MIKE: It's a fucking phone.

1266
01:46:41,174 --> 01:46:44,000
-You could have broken it.
-You're a fucking idiot.

1267
01:46:44,010 --> 01:46:45,969
Oh, fuck.

1268
01:46:45,979 --> 01:46:48,505
MIKE: Oh, shit.
-Do not stop! Do not fucking stop!

1269
01:46:48,515 --> 01:46:51,808
MIKE: What do I do?
-Speed up! Speed up!

1270
01:46:51,818 --> 01:46:53,818
[THUD]

1271
01:46:59,859 --> 01:47:02,352
BONNER: What are you doing?
MIKE: Dad?

1272
01:47:02,362 --> 01:47:05,088
Get back in the fucking vehicle, Mike!

1273
01:47:05,098 --> 01:47:08,258
Mike, get back in the fucking vehicle!

1274
01:47:08,268 --> 01:47:10,268
MIKE:
Daddy?

1275
01:47:17,077 --> 01:47:20,137
BONNER:
Let's go, Mike, now!

1276
01:47:20,914 --> 01:47:23,740
MIKE [OVER PHONE]:
Are you there, Dad?

1277
01:47:23,750 --> 01:47:25,809
I can hardly hear you.

1278
01:47:27,620 --> 01:47:29,045
You gotta get me out of here.

1279
01:47:29,055 --> 01:47:31,055
[SNIFFLING]

1280
01:47:31,458 --> 01:47:34,263
Well, that's just nerves talking.

1281
01:47:36,363 --> 01:47:38,854
Something happened, Dad.

1282
01:47:43,136 --> 01:47:45,136
[MIKE CRYING]

1283
01:47:48,041 --> 01:47:50,041
For Christ's sake.

1284
01:47:51,111 --> 01:47:52,936
[SIGHS]

1285
01:47:52,946 --> 01:47:55,156
Is anybody there with you?

1286
01:47:57,417 --> 01:47:59,417
No, I'm alone.

1287
01:48:02,622 --> 01:48:04,622
That's good.

1288
01:48:05,992 --> 01:48:08,790
Okay, Daddy, I, um-- I gotta go.

1289
01:48:10,997 --> 01:48:12,997
You be safe, son.

1290
01:48:13,066 --> 01:48:15,066
Stay safe.

1291
01:48:16,169 --> 01:48:19,002
Yeah. You too.

1292
01:48:21,141 --> 01:48:23,141
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

1293
01:48:41,528 --> 01:48:44,395
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING]

1294
01:48:48,134 --> 01:48:52,495
You know, my son's been driving me crazy
ever since you came over.

1295
01:48:52,505 --> 01:48:54,769
He wants a slingshot.

1296
01:48:56,142 --> 01:48:58,142
HANK:
Hmm.

1297
01:48:59,312 --> 01:49:02,882
Guess it could be worse.
Could be a BB gun.

1298
01:49:21,034 --> 01:49:23,034
[HANK SIGHS]

1299
01:49:29,676 --> 01:49:30,900
Thank you.

1300
01:49:30,910 --> 01:49:32,910
[ENGINE STARTS]

1301
01:51:23,089 --> 01:51:26,649
SANDERS: So every day,
Goliath would walk into the valley...

1302
01:51:26,659 --> 01:51:30,186
...to challenge someone, anyone.

1303
01:51:30,863 --> 01:51:33,161
But no one would fight him.

1304
01:51:33,800 --> 01:51:35,995
Until David showed up...

1305
01:51:36,169 --> 01:51:39,162
...and said, "You know what?
I'll do it. I'll fight him."

1306
01:51:39,172 --> 01:51:43,166
So the king dressed David up
in his own armor, which was so big--

1307
01:51:43,176 --> 01:51:47,001
DAVID:
But why would he let him fight a giant?

1308
01:51:47,513 --> 01:51:49,538
He was just a boy.

1309
01:51:52,285 --> 01:51:54,685
I don't know, sweetheart.

1310
01:51:56,389 --> 01:51:58,823
Do you think he was scared?

1311
01:51:59,759 --> 01:52:01,759
David?

1312
01:52:05,131 --> 01:52:06,723
Hm.

1313
01:52:06,733 --> 01:52:08,658
SANDERS:
Yeah.

1314
01:52:08,668 --> 01:52:12,153
I think he would have been really scared.

1315
01:53:02,722 --> 01:53:05,442
-Just like that?
-Just like that.

1316
01:53:05,758 --> 01:53:07,817
It looks really old.

1317
01:53:08,695 --> 01:53:10,890
It's been well used.

1318
01:53:21,240 --> 01:53:23,266
And I shouldn't take it down at night?

1319
01:53:23,276 --> 01:53:25,276
No.

1320
01:53:26,446 --> 01:53:28,826
You leave it just like that.

1321
01:53:30,249 --> 01:53:32,547
-That's a lot easier.
-Hm.

